//Tips Different Screen sizes are as follows
xlarge screens are at least 720dp x 960dp large screens are at least 480dp x 640dp normal screens are at least 320dp x 470dp small screens are at least 320dp x 426dp
If you want to add different sizes of images, put them in following folder accordingly, Android OS will automatically take the most suitable image out of them.
res/drawble-ldpi/my_image.png res/drawble-mdpi/my_image.png res/drawble-hdpi/my_image.png res/drawble-xhdpi/my_image.png
If you want to make application which support for multiple devices, also you have to create different layout directories for put different layouts.
res/layout/my_layout.xml res/layout-small/my_layout.xml res/layout-large/my_layout.xml res/layout-xlarge/my_layout.xml
